, Oxfordshire, Warwickshire, and Shropshire, or from any residence at a cottage in or near a wood."],"variants":[{"name":"Woodcox","meanings":["English: variant of   Woodcock  ."]}]},{"name":"Gilbert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. This was the name of the founder of the only native British religious order (abolished at the Dissolution of the Monasteries),  St Gilbert  of Sempringham (  ?1083–1189 ), in whose honour it is still sometimes bestowed, especially among Roman Catholics. It gained a wider currency in the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Gilbert Woodcock was born in 1216, in Cuerden, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom as the son of William Woodcock. He married Mrs. Gilbert Woodcock about 1241, in Cuerden, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1216–":"1216–Surnud","1216–Male":"1216–Surnud","1223–Female":"1223–Surnud","1241–1291":"1241–1291","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1216":"1216","ABT 1241":"umbes 1241","1223":"1223","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1175":"1175","1291":"1291","Cuerden, Leyland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Cuerden, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warrington, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Warrington, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of, Cuerden, Lancashire, England":"Cuerden, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cuerden, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Cuerden, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1216–":"1216–Kuollut","1216–Male":"1216–Kuollut","1223–Female":"1223–Kuollut","1241–1291":"1241–1291","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1216":"1216","ABT 1241":"noin 1241","1223":"1223","1220":"1220","1241":"1241","1175":"1175","1291":"1291","Cuerden, Leyland, Lancashire, Eng